6 PART I. PROVIDE FOR OFFICER EXCULPATION
7 SECTION 1. G.S. 55-2-02 reads as rewritten:
8 "§ 55-2-02. Articles of incorporation.
9 …
10 (b) The articles of incorporation may set forth any provision that under this Chapter is
11 required or permitted to be set forth in the bylaws, and may also set forth any or all of the
12 following:
13 (1) The names and addresses of the individuals who are to serve as the initial
14 directors.
15 (2) Provisions not inconsistent with law regarding (i) the purpose or purposes for
16 which the corporation is organized; (ii) managing the business and regulating
17 the affairs of the corporation; (iii) defining, limiting, and regulating the powers
18 of the corporation, its board of directors, and shareholders; (iv) a par value for
19 authorized shares or classes of shares; (v) the imposition of personal liability
20 on shareholders for the debts of the corporation to a specified extent and upon
21 specified conditions; and (vi) any limitation on the duration of the corporation.
22 (3) A provision limiting or eliminating the personal liability of any director
23 arising out of an action whether by or in the right of the corporation or
24 otherwise for monetary damages for breach of any duty as a director. director
25 or limiting or eliminating the personal liability of any officer arising out of an
26 action for monetary damages for breach of any duty as an officer. No such
27 provision shall be effective with respect to (i) acts or omissions that the
28 director or officer at the time of such the breach knew or believed were clearly
29 in conflict with the best interests of the corporation, (ii) in the case of a
30 director, any liability under G.S. 55-8-33, (iii) any transaction from which the
31 director or officer derived an improper personal benefit, or (iv) acts or
32 omissions occurring prior to the date the provisions provision became
33 effective. effective, or (v) in the case of an officer, any claim by or in the right
34 of the corporation. As used herein, in this subdivision, the term "improper
35 personal benefit" does not include a director's reasonable compensation or
36 other reasonable incidental benefit for or on account of his the director's
