1 (c) If the issuing corporation is authorized to issue different classes of shares or different
2 series within a class, the designations, relative rights, preferences, and limitations applicable to
3 each class and the variations in rights, preferences, and limitations determined for each series
4 (and the authority of the board of directors to determine variations for future series) must shall
5 be summarized on the front or back of each certificate. Alternatively, each certificate may state
6 conspicuously on its front or back that the corporation will furnish the shareholder this
7 information on request in writing and without charge.
8 (d) Each share certificate (1) must (i) shall be signed (either manually or in facsimile) by
9 two officers designated in the bylaws or by the board of directors and (2) (ii) may bear the
10 corporate seal or its facsimile.
11 (e) If the person who signed in any capacity (either manually or in facsimile) a share
12 certificate no longer holds office when the certificate is issued, the certificate is nevertheless
13 valid."
