15 PART V. CLARIFY AND REVISE DERIVATIVE PROCEEDING PROCEDURES
16 SECTION 5.(a) G.S. 55-7-40.1 reads as rewritten:
17 "§ 55-7-40.1. Definitions.
18 In this Part:
19 (1) "Derivative proceeding" means a civil suit in the right of a domestic
20 corporation or, to the extent provided in G.S. 55-7-47, in the right of a foreign
21 corporation.corporation, to recover for an injury to the corporation.
22 (2) "Shareholder" has the same meaning as in G.S. 55-1-40 and includes a
23 beneficial owner whose shares are held in a voting trust or held by a nominee
24 on the beneficial owner's behalf."
25 SECTION 5.(b) G.S. 55-7-42 reads as rewritten:
26 "§ 55-7-42. Demand.
27 No shareholder may commence a derivative proceeding until:until both of the following have
28 occurred:
29 (1) A written demand has been made upon delivered to the corporation to take
30 suitable action; andaction. The written demand shall describe in reasonable
31 detail the reasons for the demand and the action being requested and state that
32 the shareholder may commence a derivative proceeding if the action is not
33 taken. If the shareholder is a beneficial shareholder or an unrestricted voting
34 trust beneficial owner, the written demand shall be accompanied by evidence
35 of the beneficial ownership.
36 (2) 90 days have expired from the date the demand was made unless, prior to the
37 expiration of the 90 days, the shareholder was notified that the corporation
38 rejected the demand, or unless irreparable injury to the corporation would
39 result by waiting for the expiration of the 90-day period."
40 SECTION 5.(c) G.S. 55-7-44 reads as rewritten:
41 "§ 55-7-44. Dismissal.
42 (a) The court shall dismiss a derivative proceeding on motion of the corporation if a
43 determination is made, whether before or after the commencement of the derivative proceeding,
44 by one of the groups specified in subsection (b) or (f) of this section determines of this section in
45 good faith faith, after conducting a reasonable inquiry upon which its conclusions are based
46 based, that the maintenance of the derivative proceeding is not in the best interest of the
47 corporation.
48 (b) Unless a panel is appointed pursuant to subsection (f) of this section, the The inquiry
49 and determination in subsection (a) of this section shall be made by:by any of the following:
50 (1) A majority vote of independent directors present at a meeting of the board of
51 directors if the independent directors constitute a quorum; orquorum.
