30 PART VII. CLARIFY PROVISIONS FOR MERGERS BETWEEN PARENT ENTITIES
31 AND SUBSIDIARY CORPORATIONS
32 SECTION 7.(a) G.S. 55-11-04(f) is repealed.
33 SECTION 7.(b) G.S. 55-11-12 reads as rewritten:
34 "§ 55-11-12. Merger between parent unincorporated entity and subsidiary corporation or
35 corporations.
36 (a) Subject to the other provisions of this section and Article 9 of this Chapter, a parent
37 unincorporated entity owning shares of a domestic subsidiary corporation that carry at least
38 ninety percent (90%) of the voting power of each class and series of the outstanding shares of the
39 subsidiary corporation and that have the power to vote in the election of directors at the time of
40 a merger under this section may merge the subsidiary corporation or corporations into itself, or
41 merge itself and one or more subsidiary corporations into another subsidiary corporation, without
42 approval of the board of directors or shareholders of the subsidiary corporation or corporations,
43 unless the articles of incorporation for of the subsidiary corporation or corporations require
44 approval of the shareholders of the subsidiary corporation or corporations, if both all of the
45 following requirements are met:
46 (1) The merger is permitted by the laws of the state or country governing the
47 organization and internal affairs of each merging business entity.
48 (2) Each merging business entity complies with the requirements of this section
49 and, to the extent applicable, the laws referred to in subdivision (1) of this
50 subsection.
